Popyrin, who recently told ATPTour.com that he wanted to find consistency in his results by staying in baseline rallies longer by using his mobility, hit 30 winners to 24 unforced errors, while Rune hit 24 winners and 39 unforced errors, according to Infosys ATP Stats.

